description.1: Jane's whereabouts are finally discovered in Runestaff! Plus, Keith Kincaid makes a shocking revelation about Kamo Tharnn.
description.2: Doctor Doom seeks a suitable host for the power he has stolen from the Silver Surfer. Will he find an eligible candidate with the same degree of vengefulness?
description.3: Wolverine and Rogue crack some Yakuza skulls in a Ginza District bar. Their goal: to pick up the trail that will lead them to the Silver Samurai and Viper!
description.4: Cloak and Dagger plus the Punisher against the Kingpin. Can Spider-Man prevent the situation from turning deadly?
description.7: It's a mix of emotions for Ben and the rest of the Fantastic Four, when Ben's high school love reaches out wishing to see him. How will she react to Ben's new appearance as the Thing?
description.8: Spider-Man's partner this time around is none other than the smartest man in Marvel - REED RICHARDS, MR. FANTASTIC! What is "The Common Denominator" and how does it figure into the scheme of the new and improved Everyman? Here's a hint- it has to do with Mr. Fantastic, as Reed Richards is abruptly robbed of his most powerful weapon...his brilliant mind!
description.9: Dr. Strange joins forces with the Scarlet Witch and Captain Marvel to battle Dracula's minions!
description.11: Bullseye threatens to return to the criminal scene! And he may have a new inspiration in Daredevil…
description.12: Stark International, or Stane International? Tony gets a cold dose of reality when he realizes that his drinking has cost friendships and a company.
description.14: Thor, Keith and Sif set off to retrieve the mysterious Runestaff to bring Jane back to life! But even if they manage to get their hands on it, will it be enough?
description.16: The Fantastic Four put their heroic duties on hold to monitor the health of Alicia and Franklin- and attempt to rebuild a normal life. But is normalcy obtainable for the FF?
description.17: The moment the X-Men arrive in Japan for Wolverine's wedding, a fight breaks out between Yukio and the Silver Samurai! The X-Men set out to see what the fuss is all about.
description.18: Spider-Man believes Cloak and Dagger to have murdered junkies which leads to another throwdown between the heroes. Plus, the Punisher makes an appearance!
description.20: Nostalgic Daredevil fans will love this one: Go inside the Man Without Fear’s first ever comic series with a “lookahead” feature.
description.21: Can the rebels stop an interplanetary missle headed straight towards an ally planet?
description.22: After reconciling his relationship with Mary Jane, Spider-Man learns about a hostage situation in the Our Lady of Grace Chapel! He enters the church with hopes to take care of the armed men, but if they detect Spidey all will be lost!
description.23: It's the season of the witch... the Scarlet Witch that is. When a distraught Wanda takes over the Avengers Mansion, it's up to her fellow teammates and friends to calm the mad witch down. Take a look into the mind of a true witch!
description.24: It seems Cap's troubles just keep piling up. With Dum Dum Dugan hospitalized, Jeffrey Mace succumbing to his battle with cancer, and extreme violence in the city, will Cap be able to hold himself together before going mad?
description.27: Curtis Carr aids Power Man and Iron Fist in their mission to defeat the new Chemistro!
description.28: The Thing stumbles upon the new Yancy Street Gang while wandering through his old building. Telling the story of his turbulent youth, he tries to convince the gang kids that they too can quit the streets for a better life.
description.31: Enter Wolverine! Bullseye suffers extensive damage…until he is given a sliver of hope by mysterious agents.
description.32: When Tony's drinking reaches a new low, Captain America is asked to step in and stage an intervention. Meanwhile, Obadiah Stane has declared himself the de-facto CEO of Stark International.
description.34: Lady Sif succumbs to the seduction of Dracula! Can our hero defeat the vampire without causing harm to his lady love?
description.35: The Fantastic Four journey to the Negative Zone to battle Annihilus! It's a showdown you won't want to miss!
description.36: Rogue is back! But this time things are different-her powers are out of control and her absorption of Ms. Marvel's abilities is permanent! Plus, Charles Xavier's attempts to walk in his new body have proven fruitless. What is keeping him from taking his first step?
description.40: Alison and Lois fight Rogue together after going on the lam from the law!
description.41: The Mad Thinker is at it again! Transferring his consciousness into a ruthless, (and awesome) android, the villain finds out if Spidey's Spider-Sense is fact or fiction! Meanwhile, Peter Parker's love life gets turned upside down!
description.42: Annihilus has escaped and has taken the Fantastic Four captive! But before Earth's Mightiest Heroes can rescue them, they must first get through the barrier! Will our heroes prove victorious before Annihilus has his way?
description.43: After a failed attempt to defeat Viper, Cap, Dugan, Nomad, and Gail Runciter find themselves facing certain death when Viper plots to release a deadly virus into the population!
description.44: While cruising on Danny’s yacht, a mystic lure draws all on-board to a luxe island…where a pair of newlyweds are being held hostage at their own wedding!
description.45: Witness a team up between PRINCESS LEIA and a woman who has designs on none other than LUKE SKYWALKER.
description.46: MARVEL AGE speaks to “baby-faced” Bob Layton about his Marvel origin story.
description.54: Tarkington Brown, a desperate man with nothing to lose, learns the secret identity of Daredevil.
description.55: James Rhodes is still in the Iron Man armor, but he needs a crash course in the suit's tech from Stark engineer Morley Erwin.
description.58: Jane Foster has gone missing- and Donald Blake is the prime suspect! Meanwhile, Dracula rises after an undead sleep. Which Asgardian has he set his sights on?
description.60: Taranith Gelstal harnesses Reed's intellect to free himself of his bonds- leaving Reed's body lifeless!
description.61: To save the X-Men, Storm must engage the Morlock leader Callisto in a duel to the death!
description.63: Can Lando and Luke escape imprisonment from a group of bounty hunters led by IG-88 and Bossk?
description.64: It’s Chemistro vs. Chemistro, when Power Man and Iron Fist summon the help of the original alchemist, Curtis Carr!
description.66: Scarlet Witch joins the Vision and Spider-Man in New Hampshire to take down the nightmarish Necrodamus!
description.67: Dracula, the King of Vampires, makes his startling return!
description.69: Vulture flies free to exact his revenge on Bestman! Can Spider-Man recover from his previous scrape and prevent a fateful collision? Or will the Vulture take down another victim?
description.70: Captain Marvel and Starfox join the Avengers as full-fledged members! Their first mission: Take down the villain known as Plantman! Plus: Tony Stark, the former Ironed Avenger, succumbs to alcoholism!
description.71: After donning the Nomad costume, Jack Monroe and Dum Dum Dugan rush to Illinois to recue Captain America and Gail Runciter and foil the Viper's sinister plot! Will the two make a good team and save the day? Find out when Cap and company face Viper!
description.75: Marvel legends like Roger Stern and Butch Guice offer insight—and advice—on what it takes to write for Marvel Comics!
description.81: The Vulture decides to travel to the Big Apple to capture Gregory Bestman at a High Tech Expo. Spider-Man attempts to prevent the worst from happening! Can he stop the wings of vengeance from flying away?
description.82: After a night out, Rogers and Bernie are being followed home by Jack Monroe, the 1950's Bucky. Meanwhile, Spider-Woman tracks Viper to an abandoned warehouse only fall prey to a trap. Does Bucky's reappearance have anything to do with Viper's plans?
description.84: Spider-Man and the Vision team up against a stalking serial killer who is terrorizing small towns in New Hampshire!
description.86: Dazzler uses music as a distraction to stop the robbery of ticket sales at her concert! Lois’ mutant powers manifest after a traumatic encounter.
description.88: In this special chapter of MARVEL AGE, gain insider info on the members of Canada’s premier super-team: Alpha Flight!
description.90: At the Amalgamated Chemical & Pharmaceutical Plant, the Heroes for Hire face off against Chemistro’s brother.
description.91: In the quest for Han Solo, Luke and the others track down IG-88 and Bossk, who may have info on the wherabouts of Boba Fett!
description.92: Will this be the issue when Daredevil sets aside his vigilantism?
description.93: When the villainous Magma attacks Stark International, an incapacitated Stark is unable to fight back. James Rhodes dons the Iron Man armor and rises to the occasion.
description.95: The Thunder God lies defeated by the Crusader! Will Sif and Odin's efforts restore Thor's faith towards a path of healing?
description.96: The team is ambushed in the Mantracora region of the Negative Zone...and is then kidnapped! All the while, Annihilus furthers his plot to destroy Earth. Will other heroes rise in the FF's absence?
description.97: When Angel goes missing in the catacombs beneath New York City, the X-Men head to investigate. Soon they discover the Morlocks are behind the abduction, but at that point they may already be too late...

0.text: Karma is missing in action! The New Mutants are invited on an expedition by Sunspot's mother to cheer up, but after she is kidnapped by the Hellfire Club, it is up to the team to save her!
Karma is missing in action! The New Mutants are invited on an expedition by Sunspot's mother to cheer up, but after she is kidnapped by the Hellfire Club, it is up to the team to save her!

5.text: Hulk is transported into the 41st century by "The Hero"!

6.text: Introducing Canada's premiere superhero team, Alpha Flight, as they take on the dimensional beast Tundra!

7.text: It's a mix of emotions for Ben and the rest of the Fantastic Four, when Ben's high school love reaches out wishing to see him. How will she react to Ben's new appearance as the Thing?

10.text: Hank McCoy gets a brand new puppy named Sassafras. Plus, the Elf With a Gun begins his reign of terror!

13.text: The New Mutants and Team America set off on their respective missions to save Psyche from Viper and the Silver Samurai! But to find where Psyche is being held, Karma must make a deal she may regret!
The New Mutants and Team America set off on their respective missions to save Psyche from Viper and the Silver Samurai! But to find where Psyche is being held, Karma must make a deal she may regret!

15.text: WHAT IF…DOCTOR STRANGE HAD NOT BECOME THE MASTER OF THE MYSTIC ARTS? In an alternate story, Baron Mordo inherits the full extent of the Ancient One's power.

27.text: Curtis Carr aids Power Man and Iron Fist in their mission to defeat the new Chemistro!

28.text: The Thing stumbles upon the new Yancy Street Gang while wandering through his old building. Telling the story of his turbulent youth, he tries to convince the gang kids that they too can quit the streets for a better life.

30.text: Zzzax is reborn when Stark Industries accidentally installs the wrong equipment in Banner and Lang’s lab!

33.text: The New Mutants encounter Viper and the Silver Samurai, along with Team America! But who is the Dark Rider? And are the New Mutants ready to go on a mission to rescue one of their own?
The New Mutants encounter Viper and the Silver Samurai, along with Team America! But who is the Dark Rider? And are the New Mutants ready to go on a mission to rescue one of their own?

39.text: The Defenders finally lend their ears to Patsy Walker's nightmares.

44.text: While cruising on Danny’s yacht, a mystic lure draws all on-board to a luxe island…where a pair of newlyweds are being held hostage at their own wedding!

50.text: Journalist Joy Mercado gets the scoop on two dueling street legends…Moon Knight and Druid Walsh.

53.text: The Hulk travels through time to help save the Avengers!

56.text: Professor X reveals his true motives for re-opening his School for Gifted Youngsters! And with Stevie Hunter's life being threatened, the New Mutants are on the case!
Professor X reveals his true motives for re-opening his School for Gifted Youngsters! And with Stevie Hunter's life being threatened, the New Mutants are on the case!

62.text: The Final Battle! Doc Ock is back again and it's revenge or death! And in prison, the Punisher has an offer for Boomerang - help him escape or be punished!

64.text: It’s Chemistro vs. Chemistro, when Power Man and Iron Fist summon the help of the original alchemist, Curtis Carr!

68.text: Daimon thought he knew who he was when he rid himself of his Satanic heritage. Now? He has no idea who he has become.

72.text: The dramatic conclusion of the Master of Kung Fu's story!

76.text: A New Dawn... a New World!

77.text: Marvel super heroes battle…against one another?!

79.text: The Avengers, the Hulk and She-Hulk are fooled by the Leader at his space station, where he sends the Avengers hurdling through time!

85.text: Doctor Strange appears in…"The Light That Never Was!" Digital issue omits "Wolf-Boy", published in Marvel Illustrated: Jungle Book (2007) #1.

89.text: The origin of Galactus! Scientist Galan was once a resident of Taa, a peaceful planet facing imminent doom. With the universe folding in on itself, Galan is determined to be the savior of his race- but the cosmos have other plans. Galactus emerges from the chaos, and must feed on the vital forces of a dying universe!

90.text: At the Amalgamated Chemical & Pharmaceutical Plant, the Heroes for Hire face off against Chemistro’s brother.

94.text: Has Psyche gone mad, or is it the Spirit Bear out to get her? Or worse -- is Professor X really a Brood?
Has Psyche gone mad, or is it the Spirit Bear out to get her? Or worse -- is Professor X really a Brood?

98.text: Spider-Man visits a recovering Black Cat, still in fear of a returning Doc Ock looking for revenge on the pair of them. Plus, Boomerang ends up in prison…in a cell next to the Punisher!

99.text: Shang-Chi visits the temple where his father, the diabolical Fu Manchu, was trained.
